arch:property.oc:show_val: This not a sealed locus, but it is comprised of compacted beaten earth with significant numbers of architectural fragments, most important of which are fragments of plaster. It lenses into burnt deposits of Locus 8 and has ash lenses of a Munsell very dark gray 7.5YR 3/1.
Phase XII: Use levels, robbing and abandonments continue.
Closing elevation: -1.10 m below Sub datum Pt. 71 A, or 898.78 m.
The Locus 5 steps and the Byzantine Platform on the south and Locus 10 on the north.
3/4 of what has been excavated in the east side of the trench. This locus became L-shaped, measuring 2.84 m east west-by-5.70 m north south.
From the fifth column in the north to the Byzantine Wall. It lies between the Locus 10 wall on the north to the Locus 5 steps in the south.
Phase XIII: Major collapses continue into the Islamic period.
Opening elevation: - 0.10 m below Sub datum Pt. 71 A, or 899.78 m.
